# Normalise line endings to LF in the repository AND in the working tree.
#
# eol=lf on everything (not just normalisation to LF in the index) because the
# VibeTags processor itself writes generated files (example/CLAUDE.md,
# example/.cursorrules, ...) with LF line endings: under core.autocrlf=true on
# Windows those files checked out as CRLF, so every local example build left
# dozens of files "modified" in git status with an empty diff. With eol=lf the
# checkout matches what the processor writes and regeneration stays invisible.
# No file in this repo requires CRLF (no .cmd/.bat/.ps1 committed).
* text=auto eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
.github/workflows/*.yml text eol=lf
Makefile text eol=lf
